snippet.textDisplay: When Graham Norton talked about his show on Colbert (contrasting his with a regular 1-1 interview format) he mentioned that if a shy guest was on the couch (Schwimmer) and saw a more extroverted guest get a big laugh (Ruffalo) it would bring out the competition in them, and suddenly they would want to tell a funny story too with no prompting from the host.  He creates a nice party atmosphere on the couch with a great ebb and flow of focus.  No one hogs attention the whole time.  Everyone has a drink.  This really is the best talk show.
